00:46:08.065 --> 00:46:09.158
Audrey Nelson.

959
00:46:12.236 --> 00:46:13.295
Uh. yes. Yeah.

960
00:46:13.371 --> 00:46:15.465
I understand she has a
new memoir coming out.

961
00:46:15.740 --> 00:46:17.140
I'm so proud of her. it's...

962
00:46:17.975 --> 00:46:19.375
[Petra] Yeah. I read it.

963
00:46:19.877 --> 00:46:20.877
It's very good.

964
00:46:22.213 --> 00:46:26.241
But. uh. most of it centers around
the main character's relationship

965
00:46:26.317 --> 00:46:27.979
with her seminar professor.

966
00:46:28.586 --> 00:46:33.183
an aging white novelist who is
verbally and emotionally abusive.

967
00:46:33.691 --> 00:46:35.990
At one point he
literally tells her

968
00:46:36.060 --> 00:46:40.498
