in order for a woman to enjoy it.

971
00:46:51.809 --> 00:46:55.473
Noah. are you the
professor in that book?

972
00:46:56.147 --> 00:46:57.171
[sighs]

973
00:46:58.616 --> 00:47:00.209
I. I mean. possibly. I...

974
00:47:00.651 --> 00:47:02.643
But if so. then she has taken

975
00:47:03.654 --> 00:47:06.556
a few very nuanced and
complicated conversations.

976
00:47:06.624 --> 00:47:08.525
uh. completely out of context.

977
00:47:08.826 --> 00:47:10.055
I spoke to Audrey.

978
00:47:10.561 --> 00:47:12.860
Oh. okay. So that
question was rhetorical.

979
00:47:12.930 --> 00:47:15.525
She paints you as a rather
unapologetic misogynist.

980
00:47:15.666 --> 00:47:17.157
A misogynist? I...

981
00:47:19.337 --> 00:47:21.465
For fuck's sake. Petra. I was...

982
00:47:21.539 --> 00:47:23.817
I'd just gotten out of jail when
I was teaching that seminar.

983
00:47:23.841 --> 00:47:27.369
I had even attempted
suicide. so. yes.

984
00:47:27.445 --> 00:47:29.937
in my state of mind
at that time of my life.

985
00:47:30.014 --> 00:47:31.414
I was probably...

986
00:47:32.550 --> 00:47:35.213
not the greatest kind
of instructor. But...

987
00:47:37.388 --> 00:47:41.325
to tell her I wasn't responding to
her material is not a criminal act.

988
00:47:41.759 --> 00:47:43.421
She's obviously trying to...

989
00:47:43.761 --> 00:47:47.596
conflate the current political climate
with my very brief association with her

990
00:47:47.665 --> 00:47:50.499
in order to direct attention
to her book. I mean...

991
00:47:51.802 --> 00:47:53.634
[sighs] Come on. you're
an intelligent woman.

992
00:47:53.704 --> 00:47:55.138
Isn't that obvious to you?

993
00:47:58.042 --> 00:48:02.173
Audrey told me that much of
<i>Descent</i> was autobiographical.

994
00:48:02.680 --> 00:48:05.650
Your second wife. Alison
Bailey. committed suicide.

995
00:48:05.983 --> 00:48:07.281
Could that be. in any way.

996
00:48:07.351 --> 00:48:10.150
related to your depiction
of her in that book?

997
00:48:10.721 --> 00:48:12.121
[sighs]

998
00:48:16.494 --> 00:48:17.494
Noah.

999
00:48:27.605 --> 00:48:28.605
Mm-hmm.

1000
00:48:30.040 --> 00:48:32.532
Yeah. I understand. We will.

1001
00:48:34.111 --> 00:48:35.841
Well. you've been so helpful.

1002
00:48:37.915 --> 00:48:39.474
Yes. [clears throat]

1003
00:48:39.683 --> 00:48:40.981
Thank you for your time.

1004
00:48:43.287 --> 00:48:44.287
You're fucked.

1005
00:48:46.490 --> 00:48:47.490
[exhales]

1006
00:48:48.459 --> 00:48:51.019
I am having déjà vu.

1007
00:48:52.196 --> 00:48:53.196
Yeah. right.

1008
00:48:53.597 --> 00:48:57.796
How in the flying fuck did we
end up back here again. Noah?

1009
00:48:58.669 --> 00:48:59.669
I don't know.

1010
00:49:01.972 --> 00:49:03.133
What can I do. Jon?

1011
00:49:03.541 --> 00:49:04.541
[chuckles]

1012
00:49:05.643 --> 00:49:07.134
Well... [clears throat]

1013
