1090
00:53:27.771 --> 00:53:31.208
[emcee]...of the Art Seidenbaum
Award for First Fiction.

1091
00:53:32.076 --> 00:53:33.806
Armando Solis.

1092
00:53:33.877 --> 00:53:38.076
[applause]

1093
00:53:38.315 --> 00:53:41.046
[Armando] Thank you.
Thank you. <i>L. A. Times.</i>

1094
00:53:41.819 --> 00:53:46.120
English wasn't my first language.
but it was the language I chose to...

1095
00:53:46.190 --> 00:53:49.627
give voice to this
first piece of fiction.

1096
00:53:49.893 --> 00:53:51.919
this first declaration of self.

1097
00:53:51.995 --> 00:53:55.932
And I think it was the only choice.
because English makes no sense.

1098
00:53:56.200 --> 00:53:58.066
In a wonderful way. really.

1099
00:53:58.235 --> 00:54:03.230
It has less of a road
map. less... internal logic.

1100
00:54:03.574 --> 00:54:06.806
[Armando continues indistinctly]

1101
00:54:25.095 --> 00:54:27.963
